<!--
  Static page sitemap for the jpcite site/ surface.
  Generated: 2026-04-23; canonical domain is https://jpcite.com.
  Updated 2026-04-25: legal pages (privacy/tos/tokushoho) added per audit
  a30f4c848bdd242a6 — tokushoho is a Japanese e-commerce legal requirement
  (特定商取引法) and must be discoverable. priority=0.3, changefreq=yearly.
  Updated 2026-04-26: privacy/tos/tokushoho switched from noindex to
  index,follow (legal discoverability); EN privacy + EN tos added with
  hreflang pairs; audience URLs delegated entirely to sitemap-audiences.xml
  (single canonical shard).
  Updated 2026-04-26 (later): EN /en/products.html, /en/widget.html, and
  /en/alerts.html added with hreflang pairs to JP; reciprocal EN hreflang
  also added on the JP /products.html, /widget.html, /alerts.html entries.
  /en/widget/demo.html and /en/dashboard.html stay out of the sitemap
  (demo.html and dashboard.html are noindex).
  Updated 2026-04-26: EN /en/notifications.html, /en/advisors.html, and
  /en/facts.html added with hreflang pairs to JP; reciprocal EN hreflang
  also added on the JP /notifications.html, /advisors.html, /facts.html entries.
  Updated 2026-04-26: EN /en/confidence.html added with hreflang
  pair to JP; reciprocal EN hreflang added on JP /confidence.html.
  /alerts-unsubscribe.html and /en/alerts-unsubscribe.html stay out of the
  sitemap (both noindex,nofollow — confirmation surface only).
  Updated 2026-04-26: EN /en/partners.html and
  /en/prompts.html added with hreflang pairs to JP; reciprocal EN hreflang
  also added on the JP /partners.html and /prompts.html entries.
  Updated 2026-04-26: /compare.html and /en/compare.html added
  with hreflang pairs (neutral 6-service / 13-axis comparison page).
  /sources.html and /en/sources.html already present; /facts.html JP/EN
  also already present. /humans.txt already present.
  Updated 2026-04-29: /status/ live status page added (trust
  signal for prospect evaluation). Distinct from /status.html which is the
  static fallback served on DNS flip during incidents — that one stays
  noindex. The new /status/index.html polls /v1/am/health/deep + PyPI from
  the browser; index,follow so it can rank for "jpcite status" queries.

  Excluded by design:
    - /en/tokushoho.html (noindex — JP-only legal surface with EN pointer)
    - /dashboard.html, /en/dashboard.html (noindex,nofollow, login-only)
    - /widget/demo.html, /en/widget/demo.html (noindex, demo surface)
    - /success.html (noindex,nofollow, post-checkout)
    - /alerts-unsubscribe.html, /en/alerts-unsubscribe.html (noindex,nofollow, confirmation)
    - /status.html (noindex, follow — not intended to rank)

  xhtml:link hreflang pairs: JP primary, EN mirror at /en/, x-default → JP.
  See docs/i18n_strategy.md for the lightweight EN surface policy.
-->
